acy from increased\nnoise level. The average differences in DVH metrics for clinical target volumes\n(CTVs) were less than 0.2 Gy for D95% and Dmax with no statistical\nsignificance. Conclusion: These results strongly indicate the high accuracy of\nRSP maps predicted by our machine-learning-based method and show its potential\nfeasibility for proton treatment planning and dose calculation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Mar 2020 00:50:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-23"}
