{"id":"2003.09174","submitter":"Anton Rodomanov","authors":"Anton Rodomanov, Yurii Nesterov","title":"Rates of superlinear convergence for classical quasi-Newton methods","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Math. Program. (2021)","doi":"10.1007/s10107-021-01622-5","report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the local convergence of classical quasi-Newton methods for\nnonlinear optimization. Although it was well established a long time ago that\nasymptotically these methods converge superlinearly, the corresponding rates of\nconvergence still remain unknown. In this paper, we address this problem. We\nobtain first explicit non-asymptotic rates of superlinear convergence for the\nstandard quasi-Newton methods, which are based on the updating formulas from\nthe convex Broyden class. In particular, for the well-known DFP and BFGS\nmethods, we obtain the rates of the form $(\\frac{n L^2}{\\mu^2 k})^{k/2}$ and\n$(\\frac{n L}{\\mu k})^{k/2}$ respectively, where $k$ is the iteration counter,\n$n$ is the dimension of the problem, $\\mu$ is the strong convexity parameter,\nand $L$ is the Lipschitz constant of the gradient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Mar 2020 10:19:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Feb 2021 16:08:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 1 Jun 2021 16:36:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
